# YouTube Pipeline — LLM Service

Centralized FastAPI microservice that handles all LLM calls
for the YouTube automation pipeline. Supports Anthropic, OpenAI,
and Gemini with automatic fallback.

---

## Setup

### 1. Clone and enter the directory
```bash
cd llm-service
```

### 2. Create your .env file
```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and add at least one API key:
```bash
# Add whichever key(s) you currently have
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
```

### 3. Build and start
```bash
docker compose up -d --build
```

### 4. Verify it's running
```bash
# Health check
curl http://localhost:8001/health

# Full status — shows which providers are active
curl http://localhost:8001/status
```

---

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | Phase | Description |
|--------|------|-------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/v1/research/aggregate` | Phase 2 | YouTube + Reddit → 5 video ideas |
| POST | `/api/v1/script/generate` | Phase 4 | Topic → full 5-min script |
| POST | `/api/v1/analytics/interpret` | Phase 13 | Metrics → performance grade + recommendations |
| POST | `/api/v1/keywords/broaden` | Phase 7 | Failed keyword → 3 alternatives |
| GET | `/health` | — | Docker healthcheck |
| GET | `/status` | — | Provider status + config |
| GET | `/docs` | — | Swagger UI (development only) |

---

## Adding a new API key

No code changes needed. Just update `.env` and restart:

```bash
# Add key to .env
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-new-key

# Update provider order to make it primary
LLM_PROVIDER_ORDER=anthropic,openai,gemini

# Restart service — picks up new .env automatically
docker compose restart llm-service

# Verify
curl http://localhost:8001/status
```

---

## Useful commands

```bash
# Start
docker compose up -d --build

# Stop
docker compose down

# Live logs
docker compose logs -f llm-service

# Restart after .env change
docker compose restart llm-service

# Full rebuild (after code changes)
docker compose up -d --build --force-recreate

# Check health
docker compose ps

# Shell into container (debugging)
docker compose exec llm-service /bin/sh
```

---

## n8n HTTP Request node configuration

All four endpoints follow the same pattern in n8n:

```
Method:           POST
URL:              http://localhost:8001/api/v1/{endpoint}
Authentication:   None
Body Content-Type: JSON
Send Body:        JSON
```

Example for script generation:
```json
{
  "topic": "{{ $json.chosen_topic }}",
  "regenerate": false
}
```

---

## File structure

```
llm-service/
├── .env                  ← your real keys (gitignored)
├── .env.example          ← template (safe to commit)
├── .gitignore
├── .dockerignore
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml
├── requirements.txt
└── app/
    ├── main.py           ← FastAPI app + /health + /status
    ├── config.py         ← loads .env, helper methods
    ├── routers/
    │   ├── research.py   ← POST /api/v1/research/aggregate
    │   ├── script.py     ← POST /api/v1/script/generate
    │   ├── analytics.py  ← POST /api/v1/analytics/interpret
    │   └── keywords.py   ← POST /api/v1/keywords/broaden
    ├── services/
    │   ├── provider_router.py  ← LLM routing + fallback
    │   └── prompts.py          ← all prompt strings
    └── models/
        ├── research.py   ← Pydantic request/response models
        ├── script.py     ← Pydantic request/response models
        ├── analytics.py  ← Pydantic request/response models
        └── keywords.py   ← Pydantic request/response models
```